caAERS CAAERS-3666 Exception when importing Study 7380 - Re: Installation Verification Steps Bug Closed Critical Fixed Karthik Iyer Wesley Wiggins 1/27/2010 17:21 2/3/2010 10:19 Version 2.0.1 Version 2.0.1
Version 2.5		 Module 2: Web Services for local CTMS integration   0   14400 13200 1200 8%     Mac OS X 10.6.2 - Firefox 3.5 Following Setup Study instructions for caAERS installation verification:

1. Download and save the study XML file for Study 7380(https://ncisvn.nci.nih.gov/svn/caaersappdev/docs/import/2.0/study_7380.xml)
2. Click on the Administration tab and then the Import subtab.
3. Select 'Study / Protocol' from the Import drop-down list.
4. Click Browse next to the 'Data file' field and navigate to the location where study 7380 is downloaded.
5. Click Continue. <ERROR OCCURS HERE - SEE STACK TRACE BELOW>

Could not execute the remaining steps:

6. If there are no errors the study will be shown in the "Study records will be loaded" panel.
7. Click on the import button.
8. You will be taken to the search study page
9. Select the 'identifier' option and enter 7380 in the text box.
10. Click search.
11. You should be able to view the study you just imported in the search results.
12. Click on result and view the study.
13. You are now in edit study flow.
14. Click on the Personnel subtab
15. Select 'Mayo Clinic Rochester(site)' in the drop down.
16. Click on add research staff
17. Enter the name of the research staff you created earlier
18. Choose the role as subject coordinator and click save. You will get a "Information saved successfully" message.
19. Once all changes are complete, click on the overview subtab.
20. Click on the "Study setup complete" button
21. The data entry status should change to complete.

Version 2.5		 Data Sharing / Grid Services   0   43200 0 57600 133%       The initial implementation (for v2.1) will be only a partial implementation of the use case. Below is a summary of the work that should be completed:

1) Only INDs will be consumed from PA; IDEs will be ignored
2) caAERS will save the IND #.
3) The NIH Institues and NCI Divisions will be added to the caAERS organizations via groovy and will be available out-of-the-box.

5) caAERS will parse on the hyphen ("-") and consume the NIH Institute that is the IND holder
6) An "Unknown" organization with an "Unknown" investigator will be added to caAERS via groovy and will be available out-of-the-box.
7) PA does not send the organization, industry, or investigator name. In order to consume these INDs, caAERS will associate them to the above "Unknown" organization or investigator.

caAERS CAAERS-3461 Allow configuration of Mandatory, Optional, and N/A fields on capture AE screen New Feature Closed Critical Fixed Paul Baumgartner Paul Baumgartner 1/4/2010 10:49 2/7/2010 20:18   Version 2.0.1
Version 2.5		 Module 1: Adverse Event Data Capture
Module 4: Adverse Event Reporting		   0 12219_screenshot-1.jpg  216000 0 205800 95% CAAERS-3615     1. The system must allow for the mandatory, optional, and not applicable elements to be specified upon entering adverse events (i.e. the Capture AE screen).

2. [UPDATED BELOW] The configuration of the CAE screen should be established on the Study level (i.e. NOT the system level).
- This is to accomodate different CAE requirements for different studies and study sponsors.

3. [UPDATED BELOW] There will need to be a new tab added to Study called "...." [TBD]

4. This new tab will provide similar functionality to that provided in the Report Definition >> Mandatory Sections tab
- All AE related fields will be listed
- Each field will allow for toggling of Mandatory, Optional, and Not Applicable

5. [UPDATED BELOW] There will be a default configuration set for the fields on this tab that contains all of the fields current displayed.
- Mandatory - Term, Grade; Optional - Verbatim, start date, end date, attribution, hospitalization, expected, outcome; N/A - all others.
[A nice to have feature would be for the user to set the system default from this tab]

6. The defalt configuration settings will be saved with the Study when the study is first saved either by the user saving the required Details or by saving through service consumption (PA service or local web service).

7. The mandatory fields shall be displayed following the standard conventions (i.e. a red * and shaded until a valid value is entered)

8. Any business rules that reference a N/A field should be ignored (eg. Hosp required if grade > 2 should be ignored if Hosp is an N/A field).

9. [UPDATED BELOW] The configuration of these fields should be added to the caAERS local study service.

10. The "AdEERS reporting required" field should be removed from the Study Details page

11. [UPDATED BELOW] Migration scripts will also need to be created that properly update legacy studies in pre-v2.1 caAERS system. These scripts should configure the capture AE mandatory fields as follows:

12. Just to confirm and make sure that all of us are on the same page, I am summarizing the rules that I will be following to write the migrate scripts. Please take a look and reply if it looks fine or needs any changes.

Field -- Configuration
term -- Mandatory
grade -- Mandatory
verbatim -- Optional
start date -- Optional
end date -- Optional
attribution -- Optional
hospitalization -- Optional
expected -- Optional
event location -- Not Applicable
comments -- Not Applicable
outcome -- Optional (If study.adeersReporting == false)
outcome -- Not Applicable (If study.adeersReporting == true)		   100% 96% 223800 7200 237600

caAERS CAAERS-2928 Need a message to appear warning user that the will be logged out due to inactivity Improvement Resolved Critical Fixed Sameer Sawant Paul Baumgartner 9/17/2009 17:06 2/1/2010 16:19 Version 1.9.5 Version 2.0.1
Version 2.5		 Module 13: Security
User Interface		 20-Nov-09 0 11943_one.png 11940_two.png                Currently when a user's session is timed out, there is no warning. A common issue reported is that a user is timed out, returns to their caAERS, and continues working. Only upon trying to access another tab are they kicked back to the login screen. Users have lost data due to this and they get the impression that the system isn't working correctly.

We need to have a warning message that appears indicating their session will be timed out in X minutes due to inactivity. They should be able to click "OK" on the message to keep it alive. If they are away from their desk, when they return, they will see the message - click OK, and then be taken to the login page.

system.

real user.

caAERS CAAERS-2438 Develop a generic caAERS report template New Feature Resolved Critical Fixed Karthik Iyer Paul Baumgartner 7/21/2009 9:05 2/1/2010 16:18 Version 2.0 Version 2.0.1
Version 2.5		 Module 4: Adverse Event Reporting 22-Jan-10 0   144000 0 91800 64% CAAERS-3498, CAAERS-3499, CAAERS-3500, CAAERS-3501, CAAERS-3502, CAAERS-3503, CAAERS-3504, CAAERS-3529, CAAERS-3577, CAAERS-3627, CAAERS-3686     caAERS currently supports five (5) report templates (MedWatch, CIOMS (2), DCP, and AdEERS). Most organizations have their own custom report formats. caAERS needs to provide a generic report template that can contain all of the fields available in the Report Definition >> Mandatory Fields tab.

This feature should operate as follows:
- When creating (or editing) a report, there will be a new report template available to users in the drop-down (called "caAERS custom template").
- This template will be a generic template that will be rendered to users in pdf format similar to the other five report templates.
- The fields displayed on this template will consist of all mandatory and optional fields as specified in the Mandatory Fields tab.
- Fields that are "Not Applicable" on the Mandatory Fields tab will not be rendered on the report pdf.
- The Study ID, Title, Study Subject ID, Subject Organization, Report ID, Amendment #, and Date Submitted will always be included in a summary section.
- Sections for which there are only "Not Applicable" fields should not be rendered on the report pdf.
- The "Display Name" of the report definition will be rendered on the report pdf as the title of the report.
- The Report Definition UI should allow configuration of header and footer information. Substitution variables should be allowed including: "Organization Name," "Page # of #'s", "CONFIDENTIAL", "Date generated", along with the ability to add free text of a limited length.
   100% 77% 239400 68400 234000

caAERS CAAERS-1766 Add ability for a study definition to be provisional until approved New Feature Resolved Major Fixed Karthik Iyer Paul Baumgartner 2/24/2009 17:09 2/1/2010 17:20 Version 2.0 Version 2.0.1
Version 2.5		 Module 1: Adverse Event Data Capture
Module 2: Web Services for local CTMS integration
Module 4: Adverse Event Reporting		 25-Mar-09 0                 Suggestion from CALGB - need to have the ability for a study to be considered provisional until it is approved. The rationale is that a study will be loaded from a CTMS, however, there are elements that will be added manually (i.e. Other MedDRA version, solicited AEs, expected AEs, investigators, staff). A study that is provisional should NOT be able to have AE's entered for it or subjects added to it.

caAERS CAAERS-597 CSM and caAERS session factories don't share transaction. Bug Resolved Major Fixed Karthik Iyer Joshua Phillips 8/22/2008 9:41 2/1/2010 16:18 Version 1.1 Version 2.0.1
Version 2.5		 Code Base Refactoring
Module 13: Security		   0                 If you try to create a new research staff, but there is some error (e.g. an error sending the email), a CSM user will be created, but a ResearchStaff object will not. This leaves the database in an inconsistent state. The operations for creating a CSM user and a ResarchStaff object should be in the same transaction.
